CSS PROPERTIES
  - font-variant: set all font variants (font-variant-alternates, font-variant-caps, etc).
  - :focus-within: pseudo class that represents an element that has received focus or contains an element 
    that has received focus

FORM
  - fieldset tag: used to group several controls as well as labels (<label>) within a web form.
    it looks like put a box with all its border visible
  - legend tag: this is the text that is the fieldset title, it is on top in the border
  - input tag:
    *attributtes:
      - accesskey: let us creat a shortcut to focus or active that element. In linux the shortcut is
        actived with alt + shift + accesskey 
      - pattern: 
        [A-Za-zÀ-ž\s]{3,} - all character with and without accents and at least 3 characters
        [a-z0-9._%+-]+@[a-z0-9.-]+\.[a-z]{2,}$ - pattern to a valid mail with lowercase characters numbers and 
          special characters before the @ and lowercase characters number after @ and before . and ar least two
          characters after . only lowercase letter
      - aria-label: used to define a string that labels the current element. Use it in cases where a text label 
        is not visible on the screen
  - i tag: used to put icons too

  SELECTORS
  - ~: <val1> ~ <val2>: selects all element val1 that are preceded by a val2
